comments.body: https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/blob/main/app/jobs/voyager_update_job.rb simply refreshes the remote metadata from Alma, and hence, supporting this would likely just require a reimplementation for https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/blob/main/app/services/voyager_updater/event_stream.rb, https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/blob/main/app/services/voyager_updater/event.rb, and https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/blob/main/app/services/voyager_updater/dump.rb (https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/blob/main/app/models/processed_event.rb just has an ID for the event itself).

This info won't be found in bibdata events anymore, so there will have to be a new way to keep track of when the last update happened.

Let's keep this lower-priority for now.
